<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,151,439]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,189,215]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,568,189,214]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Scoparia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molestalis">
<emphasis box="[329,568,189,214]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Scoparia molestalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Song" box="[783,1008,189,215]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Song, S. M. &amp; He, M. S. (1997) Lepidoptera: Pyralidae. In: Yang, X. K. (ed.), Insect of Three Gorges of Changjiang, vol. 2. Chongqing Press. Chongqing. 1096 - 1220 pp." type="journal article" year="1997">
Song &amp; He (
<number box="[936,999,189,215]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in Hubei and Sichuan provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[151,221,226,252]" name="China" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">China</collectingCountry>
with two specimens (
<number box="[480,493,226,252]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[500,522,226,252]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="3.0">3</number>
, Longmenhe, Xingshan, Hubei Province; 
<number box="[1017,1032,226,252]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1.0">1</number>
<number box="[1039,1061,226,252]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="3.0">3</number>
, Wangerbao, Wanxian, Sichuan Province). We regard it as a misidentification of 
<taxonomicName box="[761,984,264,289]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Eudonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puellaris">
<emphasis box="[761,984,264,289]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Eudonia puellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after having checked the specimens deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[316,411,301,327]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crjh-4ne1" name="Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">IZCAS</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Song" box="[424,583,301,327]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Song, S. M. (2003) Scopariinae Guenee, 1854. In: Wang J. S., Song, S. M., Wu, Y. Y. &amp; Chen, T. M. (eds.), Fauna of Pyralidae of Wuyishan Nature Reserve in China. China Science and Technology Press. Beijing. 190 - 192 pp." type="book chapter" year="2003">
Song (
<number box="[507,574,301,327]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
also reported 
<taxonomicName box="[768,931,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Scoparia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molestalis">
<emphasis box="[768,931,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. molestalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Fujian Province of 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1299,301,327]" name="China" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">China</collectingCountry>
with eight specimens (Huanggangshan, Wuyishan, Fujian Province, 
<quantity box="[840,934,338,364]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.15" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="m" value="2150.0">2150 m</quantity>
, 
<date box="[946,1086,338,364]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2000-07-27">
<number box="[946,977,338,364]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="27.0">27</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[1019,1086,338,364]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</date>
), but they were misidentified based on the correlative specimens deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[778,869,376,402]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crjh-4ne1" name="Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">IZCAS</collectionCode>
that we have checked. Actually, they are 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Scoparia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="congestalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. congestalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
